# Api doc notes

## Trip Advisor

- Base URL: https://tripadvisor16.p.rapidapi.com/api/v1/{ENDPOINT}


### Useful Options
- flights/searchFlights={}	*
- desinationAirportCode={3 letter code} 	*
- date={}	*
- itinearyType={}	*
- sortOrder={ML_BEST_VALUE | DURATION | PRICE | EARLIEST_OUTBOUND_DEPARTURE | LATEST_OUTBOUND_DEPARTURE | EARLIEST_OUTBOUND_ARRIVAL | LATEST_OUTBOUND_ARRIVAL}*
- numAdults={} *
- numSeniors={} *
- classOfService={} *
- Optional={}
- returnDate={}  ** 
#### pseudo
-displayTo
-use fetch results
-take the chosen airport variable from the airport name variable
-display flight results based on the airport name, and date selected
-list the flight results in order from descending flight prices
-selected flights will be saved into the local storage as an array


## World Airports Directory
- Base Url : https://world-airports-directory.p.rapidapi.com/{v1}{airports}{qstring}


### Output :
-results: Array
-isActive *
-AirportName *
-city *
-country *
-Airport Code *
-citycode
-lat
-long 
-timezone **
-cityunicode
-zone 
-countrycode 
-id

- page: Num
- limit: Num
- totalPages : Num
- totalResults : Num



#### Options
 - page={page index};
 - limit={number of results per page(10 default, 20max)}
 - sortb={field:order}: field{any of fileds from JSON results} order{asc| desc}

##### Pseudcode
- displayTo for both of our API's
- call event listener for click of submit button when enterring information for the flights
- Both API's are going to fetch
- needs function to search the database, base on the location given, to pull up airports
- upon event listener, store city entry if valid into local storage and store all airport names displayed into your local storage
- clear history event listener that clears local storage
- event listener on modal for  confirm and cancel entry buttons
